Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.95,0:00:09.27,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right! Now let's move forward
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.29,0:00:12.90,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,with the sun always in our hearts
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.92,0:00:16.07,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,As power passes through our clasped hands
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.09,0:00:24.09,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,let's grab hold of our wishes
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.27,0:00:34.75,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Working together, let's ride the giant waves
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.77,0:00:41.97,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's hurry toward the excitement--\Nthere's the starting signal
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.99,0:00:48.93,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Now's the time to set sail-- let's raise anchor
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.95,0:00:56.07,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Cut through the rainbow-colored wind\Nand head for a sea of adventure
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.09,0:00:59.53,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be a journey fraught with injury
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.55,0:01:03.41,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,but what you cherish most will be right there
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.43,0:01:07.41,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,And if you get into a jam
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.43,0:01:10.46,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll always be there to protect you
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.48,0:01:14.63,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right! Now let's move forward
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.65,0:01:18.17,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,with the sun always in our hearts
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.19,0:01:21.17,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,If a storm hits, let's put\Nour arms around each other
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.19,0:01:25.68,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,and gaze at the light beyond
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.70,0:01:29.39,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,If we gather up the pieces of our dreams
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.41,0:01:32.69,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,they'll make a map leading to tomorrow
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.71,0:01:35.65,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,So let's grab hold of our wishes
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.67,0:01:41.44,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,under the same flag-- together, we're one
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.46,0:01:49.46,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,One Piece
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.94,0:02:00.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A-A frog is doing the front crawl!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.40,0:02:01.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.40,0:02:03.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It went to your side, so take a look at it!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.44,0:02:06.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Is that true?\N--Hey, Luffy...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.20,0:02:09.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you taking what that\Nstupid Admiral said seriously?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.49,0:02:12.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To start with, there's no way a frog\Nwould do the front cra... Hey, it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.58,0:02:14.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A-A frog is doing the front crawl!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.08,0:02:16.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll follow it, guys!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.25,0:02:20.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.42,0:02:25.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why is there a lighthouse in a place\Nlike that? I wonder if someone's there...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.30,0:02:28.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Heave-ho! Heave-ho! Heave-ho!...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.85,0:02:30.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It flew!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.31,0:02:38.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right! The frog stopped. Corner it at once!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.81,0:02:40.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We ran ashore on something!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.23,0:02:48.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's this sound?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.71,0:03:01.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ow, ow, ow...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.25,0:03:03.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go back! Go back! Turn 180 degrees!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.92,0:03:11.92,B1,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(2000,2000)}"The Dashing Sea Train and\Nthe City of Water, Water Seven"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.68,0:03:15.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell is that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.93,0:03:23.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just turn around! Now!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.63,0:03:47.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell is this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.55,0:03:50.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-Wh-What the hell is this lump of iron?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.84,0:03:51.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A ship?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.64,0:03:58.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No! Something shaped like\Nthis can't travel on the sea!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.64,0:04:06.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, frog! Run! What're you doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.28,0:04:17.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ahhh! It got run over!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.64,0:04:44.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The ship was puffing out smoke!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.94,0:04:51.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pirates...?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.49,0:04:54.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Grandma! Grandma! Pirates are here!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.20,0:04:57.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?! Is that true, Chimney?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.29,0:05:00.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay then, bring the Transponder Snail to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.71,0:05:02.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.37,0:05:05.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a problem.\NSomeone came out of the building.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.54,0:05:08.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're gonna call for help.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.84,0:05:10.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here it is, Grandma!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.34,0:05:12.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Err... Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.63,0:05:16.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see... What was it? I forget.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.89,0:05:23.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So she's drunk?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.35,0:05:28.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? Paille, huh? It goes good with alcohol.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.78,0:05:31.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa! This is good!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.24,0:05:34.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Chimney. This is our cat, Gonbe...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.86,0:05:36.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and Grandma Kokoro.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.32,0:05:40.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You guys aren't train robbers, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.24,0:05:43.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Luffy. I'm the man\Nwho'll be King of the Pirates.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.25,0:05:45.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Really?!\N--Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.63,0:05:47.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a funny guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.34,0:05:50.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, Chimney, that thing is a steamship, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.96,0:05:54.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But with a shape like that,\Nit can't go on a voyage.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.97,0:05:56.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've never seen something\Nlike that, have you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.84,0:05:59.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you look all over the world,\Nthis is the only place you can find it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.10,0:06:02.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a sea train called the "Puffing Tom."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.89,0:06:04.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Puffing Tom?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.27,0:06:10.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It turns paddlewheels using a steam\Nengine and runs on the sea railway.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.98,0:06:12.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Railway?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.36,0:06:15.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. It runs a little\Nbelow the surface of the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.03,0:06:18.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The train travels the same route every day,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.41,0:06:20.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,taking passengers from one island to another.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.62,0:06:23.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It carries ships and the mail as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.04,0:06:25.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's right. There really is a railway.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.04,0:06:27.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then we ran ashore on that, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.04,0:06:30.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right! There's both\Na signal and a partition.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.13,0:06:31.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's dangerous to come inside like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.71,0:06:36.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But the signal should face the other way.\NOtherwise, how do we see it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.47,0:06:40.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if it's dangerous, that guy\Nwouldn't understand, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.72,0:06:44.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't nice to send him flying.\NWe were after him, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.64,0:06:47.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What? "That guy"? Are you\Ntalking about Yokozuna?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.60,0:06:49.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yep, that front crawl frog.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.36,0:06:52.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yokozuna wouldn't die from that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.19,0:06:55.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's the source of all our\Nheadaches at this shift station.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.36,0:06:59.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He loves strength contests and\Nalways tries to defeat the sea train.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.03,0:07:00.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He'll show up again.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.45,0:07:04.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Strength contests? Oh...\NThat's why he didn't run, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.45,0:07:06.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's sure got guts.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.04,0:07:09.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Give me a break! We're having problems!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.21,0:07:12.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The rail guard was broken many times, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.04,0:07:15.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Every time he shows up, it causes\Nthe passengers a lot of trouble!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.01,0:07:18.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.22,0:07:19.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, then! I'm not gonna eat him!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.01,0:07:21.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not gonna eat a fighter!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.97,0:07:24.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You shouldn't have thought about\Neating a frog in the first place!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.52,0:07:28.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So where do you guys wanna go?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.14,0:07:33.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you're gonna take the sea train from here...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.02,0:07:38.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The town of the Spring Queen, St. Poplar...\NThe gourmet town, Pucci...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.49,0:07:43.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Carnival town, San Faldo...\NThey're all fun places.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.20,0:07:48.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you work for the Government,\Nthere's a separate, special train.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.66,0:07:51.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The gourmet town, Pucci?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.83,0:07:52.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.96,0:07:55.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the place the guys we met on the\Nuninhabited island were talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.59,0:08:01.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh... Come to think of it...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.43,0:08:03.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, we'll pick the gourmet town.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.26,0:08:05.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Obviously not!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.47,0:08:08.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since we've got our own ship,\Nwe won't take the train.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.06,0:08:09.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll just follow the log.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.27,0:08:11.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh...? Where is it pointing?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.85,0:08:13.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,East of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.15,0:08:17.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Then it must be Water Seven.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.24,0:08:22.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The train you saw earlier came\Nfrom that island's Blue Station.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.20,0:08:25.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's called the "City of Water." It's a nice place.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.37,0:08:26.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Water Seven?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.45,0:08:30.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Above all, it's a city that made\Na name for itself with its shipyard.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.67,0:08:32.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Their technology is No. 1 in the world!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.71,0:08:36.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The ships they build are the World\NGovernment's favorites! Isn't that amazing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.84,0:08:40.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see... Then there's gotta be\Nsome amazing shipwrights, right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.68,0:08:46.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not just "some"! It's a hangout\Nfor the world's best shipwrights!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.81,0:08:47.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Usopp!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.93,0:08:49.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.35,0:08:50.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right! I've decided!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.64,0:08:53.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're gonna go there and get a\Nshipwright to join our crew for sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.77,0:08:57.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, is that right? Then hold on a sec.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.73,0:09:00.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oof.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.44,0:09:03.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--What's that about?\N--Beats me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.24,0:09:07.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, then... Here's a simple map\Nof the island and a reference letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.91,0:09:13.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Give this to a guy named Iceberg\Nand ask him to fix your ship good.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.21,0:09:16.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Water Seven is a big place. Don't get lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.29,0:09:24.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Whoa!\N--Kokoro-san! You have a big heart!\NWhat a nice person you are!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.01,0:09:28.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're gonna go back to Water Seven soon, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.51,0:09:34.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. If I see you guys again, I'll treat\Nyou to a drink at my favorite bar.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.94,0:09:38.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay. I hope we'll see you guys again!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.27,0:09:44.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It'll take about a week for the log to\Nbe stored in Water Seven. Take it easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.32,0:09:47.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! Thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.12,0:09:50.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, guys! Get ready to set sail!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.75,0:09:52.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Yeah!\N--Well then, we'll get going!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.79,0:10:00.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for all your help, Kokoro-san! Chimney!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.30,0:10:06.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Be careful!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.34,0:10:09.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Watch out for the Government people!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.35,0:10:15.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yahoo! Let's go! To the city of meat! Yahoo!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.27,0:10:23.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Were you even listening?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.16,0:10:38.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm... What a nice wind!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.17,0:10:40.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We may be able to get to the city\Nof water sooner than expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.96,0:10:42.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hope so.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.71,0:10:47.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Luffy, leave the shipwright search to me.\NI'll find an incredibly pretty woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.64,0:10:49.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you an idiot?! It's a\Nshipwright we're talking about!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.60,0:10:53.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's gotta be a big guy like\Na mountain! Five meters tall!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.10,0:10:58.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But if he's too big, we don't know\Nif he could live okay on this ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.19,0:11:00.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All that matters is that he's skilled, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.48,0:11:02.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,More importantly, the question\Nis if we could find someone
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.53,0:11:05.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,crazy enough to want to be on a pirate ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.36,0:11:08.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm looking forward to it.\NWe're gonna have another new friend!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.70,0:11:13.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We were lucky to stop at the station first,\Nsince they drew a map for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.12,0:11:16.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we go to the place on the map\Nand visit the Iceberg guy...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.37,0:11:17.81,OS,,0000,0000,0000,,"Around here" "Water Seven"
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.83,0:11:18.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.58,0:11:21.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ha! Too simple to figure out!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.21,0:11:22.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa! This is like Luffy's drawing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.71,0:11:22.69,OS,,0000,0000,0000,,"Shipwright\N5 meters"
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.71,0:11:26.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, we're gonna all look for a guy like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.67,0:11:28.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If there was a guy like that, I'd run.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.55,0:11:32.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, me, too. If I had a boat,\NI'd escape to the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.05,0:11:33.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But this guy seems to be related to octopuses.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.01,0:11:35.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He might follow me to the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.60,0:11:37.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell are you guys running on about?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.44,0:11:39.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well then, guys, come here!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.15,0:11:42.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll give you some allowance for\Nthe week we're gonna stay there.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.06,0:11:43.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously?! Yaay! I'm first!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.61,0:11:45.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa! That's generous!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.48,0:11:47.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Stand in line!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.95,0:11:55.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Allowance! Allowance! Allowance!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.21,0:12:03.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter, Usopp?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.00,0:12:09.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This tinplate patchwork brings back\Nmemories of battles and adventure.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.97,0:12:14.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm filled with deep emotions when I\Nthink that she will be repaired soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.22,0:12:16.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--I do understand that, but...\N--Hm...?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.35,0:12:21.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...especially since we entered the Grand Line, our journey has taken quite a toll on the Merry.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.02,0:12:24.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The deck squeaks and the leakage at\Nthe bottom of the ship is bad as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.65,0:12:28.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we don't do anything, both we\Nand the ship will be in danger.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.15,0:12:31.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, but we've got tons of money now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.45,0:12:35.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can have her repaired perfectly.\NWe can power her up, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.62,0:12:37.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right! Let's get more cannons!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.24,0:12:39.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, let's get a bronze statue on board, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.50,0:12:41.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, isn't that the one?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.33,0:12:44.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.79,0:12:49.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The island! We can see the island!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.47,0:12:51.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, guys! Paddle!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.55,0:12:59.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We've got enough wind.\NDon't make us waste our energy!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.11,0:13:07.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How wonderful...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.86,0:13:14.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Amazing...!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.37,0:13:22.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell is this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.25,0:13:29.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a huge fountain!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.34,0:13:32.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Amazing! This is indeed an industrial city!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.17,0:13:33.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's no surprise that this\Nplace would have a sea train.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.63,0:13:37.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow... This is a lot of water!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.47,0:13:40.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where is that water springing out from?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.14,0:13:43.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How interesting... It looks like\Nthe water comes from the fountain,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.52,0:13:50.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,goes through the canals and falls into the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.07,0:13:53.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, do you wanna race on those water slides?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.36,0:14:00.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Race?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.16,0:14:02.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No! There's no way I'm doing that!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.62,0:14:05.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dream on, you idiot. You can't even swim.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.33,0:14:06.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.42,0:14:09.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,More importantly,\Nwhat do those numbers mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.21,0:14:10.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh...?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.01,0:14:14.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Don't know.\N--Are they walls? Or...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.84,0:14:14.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I bet those are the entrances\Nfor the five-meter shipwrights.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.84,0:14:18.70,OS,,0000,0000,0000,,"Shipwright\N5 meters"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.72,0:14:21.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a bunch of them?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.14,0:14:23.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The one up front must be the station.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.89,0:14:27.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It says Blue Station.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.56,0:14:29.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder where the harbor is.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.06,0:14:31.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It must be in the town.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.23,0:14:34.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Hey, you guys!\N--Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.03,0:14:37.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not good for you pirates\Nto be openly sailing in the front!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.24,0:14:40.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go around to the backstreets over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.49,0:14:48.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay! Thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.67,0:14:51.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa, this is amazing! A city on the water?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.05,0:14:59.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow! This place is cool! What a beautiful city!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.22,0:15:08.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But the city is flooded.\NThe houses are submerged in the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.23,0:15:12.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not it. The city was designed\Nwith the base being submerged.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.69,0:15:16.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Huh?\N--Look at the foundation\Nunderneath the buildings.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.45,0:15:18.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're right! The pillars are built higher!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.86,0:15:22.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see... That's why it's called\Nthe city of water, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.79,0:15:26.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, hurry up and dock the ship!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.62,0:15:27.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.33,0:15:31.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, hey, you guys!\NPirate ships shouldn't come in here!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.96,0:15:33.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What'd you come here for?! To plunder?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.96,0:15:36.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No! We wanna get our ship repaired!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.63,0:15:38.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Would people normally ask\Nif we're here to plunder?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.72,0:15:43.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, there's a cape ahead of here,\Nso anchor your ship there for now!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.97,0:15:45.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.31,0:15:47.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.06,0:15:48.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Again?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.48,0:15:53.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It can't be helped, right? We're pirates, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.11,0:15:55.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This area should be okay, don't you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.32,0:15:58.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In any case, what a dull place this is.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.78,0:16:06.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, then! Furl the sail!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.12,0:16:11.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What're you doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.50,0:16:17.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing! I just pulled the rope!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.72,0:16:23.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Holy crap! The Going Merry\Nhas gotten this rickety?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.80,0:16:27.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, why aren't the people\Non this island scared of pirates?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.14,0:16:30.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Probably because pirates are just\Nanother customer to their shipyard.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.64,0:16:33.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop talking and fix it already!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.40,0:16:36.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe because they have\Nbodyguards strong enough
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.28,0:16:38.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to deal with pirates who cause a ruckus?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.36,0:16:41.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They probably do...\Nconsidering the size of the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.57,0:16:45.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?! Hey, what're we gonna do? This is bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.20,0:16:47.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would it be bad? We're customers.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.75,0:16:48.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.91,0:16:50.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, then! See you later!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.66,0:16:53.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, Luffy! Usopp!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.83,0:16:56.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You guys, come with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.42,0:16:58.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.80,0:17:00.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To where?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.09,0:17:03.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First, we'll take the reference\Nletter from Kokoro-san
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.18,0:17:05.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and go find the man named Iceberg.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.22,0:17:08.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll ask him to help us\Narrange the ship's repair.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.72,0:17:11.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We also have to find a place\Nwhere we can cash in our gold.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.85,0:17:17.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see... All right, then! Anyway,\Nlet's go! To the city of water!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.69,0:17:19.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're forgetting the gold.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.74,0:17:22.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.74,0:17:26.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Zoro! Make sure you fix it good!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.41,0:17:29.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Be careful, Nami-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.50,0:17:33.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ahh... I somehow missed\Nthe chance to go with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.04,0:17:35.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go out together later.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.17,0:17:37.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?! I wonder if they have a bookstore.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.92,0:17:41.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure they do.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.47,0:17:44.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't we go to the\Nmoney-changing shop first?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.26,0:17:46.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why? Let's go to the shipyard.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.55,0:17:51.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But we can't walk around the island\Nwith this much gold. I get nervous.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.77,0:17:54.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even after changing it to money,\Nthe value is the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.23,0:17:58.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's true, but it being this big will\Nattract people's attention, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.15,0:17:59.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What if we run into bad thieves?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.78,0:18:01.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're the thieves!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.44,0:18:05.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's got a point. If we change it\Nto bills, we can all carry them.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.82,0:18:08.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm? Your remark had a sting to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.91,0:18:11.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It sounds like me carrying it is a problem!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.33,0:18:13.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. You might drop it somewhere or lose it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.79,0:18:15.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, he would. It's Luffy we're talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.75,0:18:18.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?! You guys! Don't you trust me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.96,0:18:22.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Nope!\N--Ah... Ahh... Ahh... That really hurt!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.46,0:18:26.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I may not be able to recover from thi-- Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.14,0:18:30.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this the only entrance to the city?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.76,0:18:32.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A rental bull shop?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.39,0:18:33.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.64,0:18:35.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do they rent out?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.64,0:18:37.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's "bull"?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.06,0:18:40.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Beats me. Bulldogs?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.07,0:18:41.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can't be, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.02,0:18:43.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me! Please let us rent bulls!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.65,0:18:46.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ask what they are first!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.86,0:18:49.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome! You wanna rent bulls, right?\NHow many are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.45,0:18:50.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Three!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.58,0:18:52.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of bulls would you like?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.91,0:18:55.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There're three ranks.\N"Yagara," "Rabuka," and "King."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.41,0:18:58.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, for the three of you,\Ntwo Yagaras would probably do.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.67,0:19:00.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay! Please roast them nice and tasty!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.59,0:19:02.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Weird! That conversation is weird!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.84,0:19:05.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? You followed logs to get here?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.55,0:19:08.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Yep.\N--That's quite an achievement, you guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.80,0:19:10.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then you had no idea what bulls were, did you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.76,0:19:14.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Right.\N--Well, to make a long\Nstory short, those are bulls.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.47,0:19:17.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're Yagara bulls.\NThey're everywhere in town.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.52,0:19:21.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In this area, there's a fish called\NYagara that swims with its head out.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.52,0:19:25.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the city of water.\NThere're more canals than walkways.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.61,0:19:29.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So bulls are a means of transportation\Nnecessary to the residents here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.53,0:19:31.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the same when you go\Nsightseeing on this island.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.83,0:19:34.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That fish is pulling a boat?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.08,0:19:37.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rather than pulling, they're letting\Npeople ride on their back.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.04,0:19:40.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it's like horseback riding\Nor riding in a carriage on land...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.71,0:19:43.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oof.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.34,0:19:47.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You see the fish pen there?\NWell, try and ride on it. It's comfortable.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.67,0:19:51.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be 2,000 Berries for two\Ntwo-passenger Yagara bulls.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.60,0:19:52.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, they're cute!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.80,0:19:56.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a fish that looks like a horse.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.77,0:20:01.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You jerk! What'd you do that for?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.23,0:20:09.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? He must like you. Let's get him for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.86,0:20:12.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can he carry heavy stuff okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.82,0:20:17.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Their power is incredible!\NYou can even use them for moving.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.16,0:20:19.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That bag, huh? What's inside?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.41,0:20:21.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gold.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.58,0:20:24.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're funny. Whatever it is, it'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.29,0:20:26.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--See?\N--Whoa! Give me some!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.26,0:20:27.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.34,0:20:29.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What an awfully honest old guy...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.09,0:20:32.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You too! Don't show it to others so lightly!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.05,0:20:34.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why? It wouldn't hurt, would it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.05,0:20:36.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My, my... What a surprise...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.43,0:20:39.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, then... it'll be a million\NBerries for two Yagara bulls.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.85,0:20:41.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, the price went up, pops.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.81,0:20:43.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry. It'll be five million Berries.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.94,0:20:46.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It went up even more!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.90,0:20:47.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You noticed?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.99,0:20:50.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Geez... We can't be too careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.24,0:20:51.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here, 2,000 Berries.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.41,0:20:52.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.74,0:20:55.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, are there any\Nmoney-changing shops around here?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.49,0:20:59.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, there are, but with that amount of gold,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.08,0:21:02.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the shops around here probably\Nwouldn't have enough money.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.37,0:21:04.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You should go to the downtown\Narea of the shipbuilding island.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.58,0:21:08.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The downtown area of the\Nshipbuilding island? Where is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.42,0:21:11.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's over there. Take this with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.97,0:21:13.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A map?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.89,0:21:15.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This'll be helpful! Thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.14,0:21:18.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pops, is the shipyard there, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.27,0:21:20.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. The world's No. 1 shipyard!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.77,0:21:24.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's perfect. Once we get the money,\Nwe can go to the shipyard right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.65,0:21:28.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. We can finally have\Nthe Going Merry repaired!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.90,0:21:32.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And we'll find a shipwright, too!\NI'm getting excited!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.24,0:21:34.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Well, then...\N--Shall we...?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.61,0:21:39.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right! Go! Yagara!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.24,0:21:42.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for your business! Be careful!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.87,0:21:45.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dash to the shipyard!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.79,0:21:53.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yahoo!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.98,0:22:09.09,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,A piece of a dream that we started grasping
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.11,0:22:12.63,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Chasing after something constant
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.65,0:22:18.22,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,We send our aspirations sailing into the sky
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.24,0:22:20.52,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Even when we're exhausted
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.54,0:22:23.69,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,We have a compass that can\Nsearch for something constant
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.71,0:22:29.11,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, do you think we can keep it forever?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.13,0:22:32.03,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,At the end of the dream\Nthat we will reach someday
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.05,0:22:35.07,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,We want to be adults as we\Nare now as much as possible
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.09,0:22:37.78,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,We pray to this endless sky that we look up at
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.80,0:22:40.87,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Eternally... Eternally...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.89,0:22:43.66,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Wild fantasies from our childhood
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.68,0:22:46.50,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,We trace unforgettable memories
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.52,0:22:52.17,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,And try to keep the embers\Nburning that still consume us
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.19,0:22:55.09,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,To this familiar sunny sky
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.11,0:22:57.80,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Together we entrust our feelings
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.82,0:23:00.39,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,We go beyond the changing time
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.41,0:23:08.41,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Eternally... Eternally...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.46,0:23:13.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa! This is fun!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.09,0:23:14.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's amazing that such a\Nconvenient creature exists!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.80,0:23:16.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't rock much. It's comfortable!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.76,0:23:19.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa! The canals even go above the rooftops!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.72,0:23:21.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've never seen such a huge town before!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.39,0:23:23.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. This is a town built around canals!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.72,0:23:26.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Water Seven is getting me fired up!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.31,0:23:27.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the next episode of One Piece!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.98,0:23:31.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Adventure in the City on the Water!\NHead to the Mammoth Shipbuilding Plant"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.57,0:23:39.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna be King of the Pirates!!
